### 03 — HTTP methods playground
# Open this file in IntelliJ and click the green ▶ next to each request.
# (Or copy the equivalent curl from the README.)
#
# Auth is via headers on EVERY protected call: X-Username + X-Password.
# Built-in admin: admin / admin123

@host = http://localhost:8081

### LOGIN as admin (headers) — proves your credentials work
GET {{host}}/api/login
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123

### Create a course (POST + JSON body) — admin only
POST {{host}}/api/courses
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Intro to Spring",
  "active": true
}

### Create a second, INACTIVE course
POST {{host}}/api/courses
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Advanced Databases",
  "active": false
}

### List ALL courses (GET)
GET {{host}}/api/courses
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123

### List only ACTIVE courses (query parameter)
GET {{host}}/api/courses?active=true
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123

### Get one course by id (path variable) — change the 1 if needed
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123

### Update a course (PUT + path variable + JSON body)
PUT {{host}}/api/courses/2
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "active": true
}

### Create a student (POST) — admin only
POST {{host}}/api/users
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "amir",
  "password": "secret"
}

### List users — admin only
GET {{host}}/api/users
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123

### ---- Now act as the student "amir" ----

### Student enrolls in course 1 (POST + path variable, student's own headers)
POST {{host}}/api/courses/1/enroll
X-Username: amir
X-Password: secret

### Student's own courses
GET {{host}}/api/me/courses
X-Username: amir
X-Password: secret

### Student drops course 1 (DELETE)
DELETE {{host}}/api/courses/1/enroll
X-Username: amir
X-Password: secret

### A student trying an admin-only action → 403 Forbidden
POST {{host}}/api/courses
X-Username: amir
X-Password: secret
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Should Fail",
  "active": true
}

### Wrong password → 401 Unauthorized
GET {{host}}/api/courses
X-Username: admin
X-Password: wrong

### Delete a course (DELETE) — admin only
DELETE {{host}}/api/courses/2
X-Username: admin
X-Password: admin123
